# 🧠 Mental Health Analysis in Tech Industry

## 📌 Project Overview
This project analyzes mental health trends in the tech industry using a real-world survey dataset. The goal is to understand factors affecting mental health and predict whether individuals seek treatment.

---

## 🎯 Objectives
- Analyze mental health trends among tech employees  
- Identify key factors influencing treatment-seeking behavior  
- Understand workplace impact on mental health  
- Build a machine learning model to predict treatment  

---

## 📊 Dataset Information
The dataset is based on a 2014 survey on mental health in the tech workplace.

### Features include:
- Age, Gender, Country  
- Family history of mental illness  
- Work interference  
- Company size  
- Remote work  
- Mental health benefits  
- Workplace support & awareness  

---

## 🧹 Data Preprocessing
- Handled missing values  
- Cleaned inconsistent gender values  
- Removed age outliers  
- Dropped irrelevant columns  

---

## 📈 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

### 🔹 Univariate Analysis
- Age distribution  
- Gender distribution  
- Treatment frequency  

### 🔹 Bivariate Analysis
- Treatment vs Family History  
- Treatment vs Benefits  
- Treatment vs Work Interference  

### 🔹 Multivariate Analysis
- Correlation Heatmap  
- Pairplot  
- Country-wise comparison  

---

## 📊 Key Insights
- Individuals with family history are more likely to seek treatment  
- Workplace support significantly increases treatment rates  
- Mental health is not treated equally as physical health  
- Employees are often uncomfortable discussing mental health  

---

## 🤖 Machine Learning Model
- Model Used: Logistic Regression  
- Goal: Predict whether a person seeks treatment  
- Evaluation Metrics:
  - Accuracy Score  
  - Confusion Matrix  
  - Classification Report  

---

## 🚀 Business Recommendations
- Provide mental health benefits  
- Promote wellness programs  
- Encourage open discussions  
- Train managers for mental health support  
- Ensure employee anonymity  

---

## 🏁 Conclusion
Mental health in the tech industry is influenced by both personal and organizational factors. Companies must adopt proactive strategies to create a supportive and stigma-free environment.

---

